docs: - Specify transfer event.
events.label: Transfer

docs: - Specify approval event.
events.label: Approval

docs: This function let NFT Contract Owner to mint a new NFT without providing NFT Traits/Attributes
messages.label: mint

docs: This function let NFT Contract Owner to mint a new NFT with NFT Traits/Attributes
messages.label: mint_with_attributes

docs: Transfers ownership of the contract to a `new_owner`.
Can only be called by the current owner.
On success a `OwnershipTransferred` event is emitted.
# Errors
Panics with `CallerIsNotOwner` error if caller is not owner.
Panics with `NewOwnerIsZero` error if new owner's address is zero.
messages.label: Ownable::transfer_ownership

docs: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call
owner's functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.
NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner,
thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.
On success a `OwnershipTransferred` event is emitted.
# Errors
Panics with `CallerIsNotOwner` error if caller is not owner
messages.label: Ownable::renounce_ownership

docs: Returns the address of the current owner.
messages.label: Ownable::owner

docs: Returns the collection `Id` of the NFT token.
This can represents the relationship between tokens/contracts/pallets.
messages.label: PSP34::collection_id

docs: Transfer approved or owned token from caller.
On success a `Transfer` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns `TokenNotExists` error if `id` does not exist.
Returns `NotApproved` error if `from` doesn't have allowance for transferring.
Returns `SafeTransferCheckFailed` error if `to` doesn't accept transfer.
messages.label: PSP34::transfer

docs: Approves `operator` to withdraw the `id` token from the caller's account.
If `id` is `None` approves or disapproves the operator for all tokens of the caller.
On success a `Approval` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns `SelfApprove` error if it is self approve.
Returns `NotApproved` error if caller is not owner of `id`.
messages.label: PSP34::approve

docs: Returns the owner of the token if any.
messages.label: PSP34::owner_of

docs: Returns `true` if the operator is approved by the owner to withdraw `id` token.
If `id` is `None`, returns `true` if the operator is approved to withdraw all owner's tokens.
messages.label: PSP34::allowance

docs: Returns current NFT total supply.
messages.label: PSP34::total_supply

docs: Returns the balance of the owner.
This represents the amount of unique tokens the owner has.
messages.label: PSP34::balance_of

docs: Returns the attribute of `id` for the given `key`.
If `id` is a collection id of the token, it returns attributes for collection.
messages.label: PSP34Metadata::get_attribute

docs: Returns a token `Id` owned by `owner` at a given `index` of its token list.
Use along with `balance_of` to enumerate all of ``owner``'s tokens.
The start index is zero.
messages.label: PSP34Enumerable::owners_token_by_index

docs: Returns a token `Id` at a given `index` of all the tokens stored by the contract.
Use along with `total_supply` to enumerate all tokens.
The start index is zero.
messages.label: PSP34Enumerable::token_by_index

docs: This function lets NFT owner to lock their NFT. Once locked, the NFT traits (attributes) can not be changed
messages.label: Psp34Traits::lock

docs: This function sets the baseURI for the NFT contract. Only Contract Owner can perform this function. baseURI is the location of the metadata files if the NFT collection use external source to keep their NFT artwork. ArtZero uses IPFS by default, the baseURI can have format like this: ipfs://<hash_ID>/
messages.label: Psp34Traits::set_base_uri

docs: This function returns how many NFTs have been locked by its owners
messages.label: Psp34Traits::get_locked_token_count

docs: This function return the metadata location of an NFT. The format is baseURI/<token_id>.json
messages.label: Psp34Traits::token_uri

docs: This function set the attributes to each NFT. Only Contract Owner can perform this function. The metadata input is an array of [(attribute, value)]. The attributes in ArtZero platform are the NFT traits.
messages.label: Psp34Traits::set_multiple_attributes

docs: This function return the attribute name using attribute index. Beacause attributes of an NFT can be set to anything by Contract Owner, AztZero uses this function to get all attributes of an NFT
messages.label: Psp34Traits::get_attribute_name

docs: This function return the owner of the NFT Contract
messages.label: Psp34Traits::get_owner

docs: This function returns all available attributes of each NFT
messages.label: Psp34Traits::get_attributes

docs: This function check if an NFT is locked or not
messages.label: Psp34Traits::is_locked_nft

docs: This function return how many unique attributes in the contract
messages.label: Psp34Traits::get_attribute_count

docs: This function return the latest token ID, everytime new NFT is mint, last_token_id is increased by 1 in mint function. Note: This is not the same as the total supply return by the psp34 function as NFT can be burnt.
messages.label: Psp34Traits::get_last_token_id

docs: This function allow contract owner withdraw NFT to an account in case there is any NFT sent to contract by mistake
messages.label: AdminTrait::tranfer_nft

docs: This function allows contract owner to withdraw contract balance to his account.
messages.label: AdminTrait::withdraw_fee

docs: This function allow contract owner withdraw PSP22 to an account in case there is any token sent to contract by mistake
messages.label: AdminTrait::tranfer_psp22
